<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=570&amp;p=593#p593"><![CDATA[
12/11(Sat.) 7 strategies for breaking a bad habit/ Does your school matter? ...(Host: Ellen)<br /><br />New Location Address:<br />新北市板橋區民生路二段120號1F ~(莊敬公園內莊敬市民活動中心）<br />C Meeting Room<br />新埔捷運站3號出口，直走4-5分鐘<br />Please bring your own drink, the venue has hot/cold water dispenser, but doesn't sale any food and drink.<br /><br />Entry fee:<br />NT$ 20 / each person<br />--------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:10-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation 1<br />8:00-8:10 pm Break<br />8:10-8:40: Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation 2<br /><br />--------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 1: 7 strategies for breaking a bad habit<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://au.reachout.com/articles/7-strategies-for-breaking-a-bad-habit">https://au.reachout.com/articles/7-stra ... -bad-habit</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions:<br />1.Do you have any bad habit? Do you want to quit/change the bad habit? What will you do for it?<br />2.What causes you have the bad habits? (Such like lazy cause you don’t do exercise and gain weight, pressure causes you addict to smoking/alcohol/video game, friend’s influence…)<br />3.Have you ever tried the tips of the articles to change/quit your bad habits? Does it work? Please share your experience.<br />4.Do you have any good habit that you’re proud of? What is it? How do you achieve the good habit? Can you share your experience? <br /><br />Session 2: Does your school matter?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/29175">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/29175</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Questions:</span><br />1.Are you proud of your academic performances and the school where you graduated from? Why or why not?<br />2.Do you agree with the phenomenon is known as the Big Fish - Little Pond Effect? Do you have the similar experience at school or your office? Please share with us.<br />3.Expect for the school, what else do you think that it’s more important to you? (Such like your major, the future perspective, interest…)<br />4.If the time could come back, would you choose the same school/major/job? Why or why not? If you’d like to choose different school/major/job, what are they? Why? Please share with us.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=46353">Ellen Lu</a> — Tue Dec 07, 2021 2:12 pm</p><hr />
